65&ndash;81.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2010, <em>A Philosophy of Computer
Art</em>, London/New York: Routledge.</li>

<li>Maley, Corey J., 2011, &ldquo;Analog and Digital, Continuous and
Discrete&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Studies</em>, 155(1):
117&ndash;31.</li>

<li>Milli&egrave;re, Rapha&euml;l, 2022, &ldquo;Deep learning and
Synthetic Media&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em> 200, article 231.</li>

<li>Moruzzi, Caterina, 2022, &ldquo;Creative Agents: Rethinking Agency
and Creativity in Human and Artificial Systems&rdquo;, <em>Journal of
Aesthetics and Phenomenology,</em> 9(2): 245&ndash;68.</li>

<li>Moser, Shelby, 2018, &ldquo;Videogame Ontology, Constitutive
Rules, and Algorithms&rdquo;, in <em>The Aesthetics of
Videogames</em>, London: Routledge, pp. 42&ndash;59.</li>

<li>Mitchell, William J., 1994, <em>The Reconfigured Eye: Visual Truth
in the Post-Photographic Era</em>, Cambridge, MA: MIT Press.</li>

<li>Nguyen, C. Thi, 2020, &ldquo;The Arts of Action. &rdquo;
<em>Philosopher&rsquo;s Imprint</em>, 20(14): 1&ndash;27.</li>

<li>Patridge, Stephanie, 2017, &ldquo;Video Games and Imaginative
Identification&rdquo;, <em>The Journal of Aesthetics and Art
Criticism</em>, 75(2): 181&ndash;84.</li>

<li>Paul, Christiane, 2008, <em>Digital Art</em>, 2nd edition,
London/New York: Thames &amp; Hudson.</li>

<li>Paul, Elliot Samuel and Scott Barry Kaufman (eds.), 2017, <em>The
Philosophy of Creativity: New Essays</em>, New York: Oxford University
Press.</li>

<li>Piccinini, Gualtiero, 2008, &ldquo;Computers&rdquo;, <em>Pacific
Philosophical Quarterly</em>, 89: 32&ndash;73.</li>

<li>Ponech, Trevor, 2006, &ldquo;External Realism about Cinematic
Motion&rdquo;, <em>British Journal of Aesthetics</em>, 46(4):
349&ndash;68.</li>

<li>Preston, Dominic, 2014, &ldquo;Some Ontology of Interactive
Art&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy and Technology</em>, 27(2):
267&ndash;78.</li>

<li>Roberts, T. and Joel Krueger, 2022, &ldquo;Musical agency and
collaboration in the digital age&rdquo; in <em>Collaborative Embodied
Performance: Ecologies of Skill</em>, K. Bicknell and J. Sutton
(eds.), New York: Bloomsbury: 125&ndash;40.</li>

<li>Robson, Jonathan and Aaron Meskin, 2016, &ldquo;Video Games as
Self-Involving Interactive Fictions&rdquo;, <em>The Journal of
Aesthetics and Art Criticism</em>, 74(2): 165&ndash;77.</li>

<li>Robson, Jonathan and Grant Tavinor (eds.), 2018, <em>The
Aesthetics of Videogames</em>, London: Routledge.</li>

<li>Rodowick, D.N., 2007, <em>The Virtual Life of Film</em>,
Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press.</li>

<li>Rush, Michael, 2005, <em>New Media in Art</em>, London: Thames
&amp; Hudson.</li>

<li>Saltz, David S., 1997, &ldquo;The Art of Interaction:
Interactivity, Performativity, and Computers&rdquo;, <em>Journal of
Aesthetics and Art Criticism</em>, 55(2): 117&ndash;27.</li>

<li>San Francisco Museum of Modern Art (SF MoMA), n.d., &ldquo;Craig
Kalpakjian: Corridor (1995)&mdash;About the Artwork&rdquo; [Museum
Exhibit Label]. San Francisco, CA
 [<a href="https://www.sfmoma.org/artist/craig_kalpakjian/" target="other">available online</a>].</li>
 
<li>Smuts, Aaron, 2009, &ldquo;What is Interactivity?&rdquo;,
<em>Journal of Aesthetic Education</em>, 43(4): 53&ndash;73.</li>

<li>Straeubig, Michael and Sebastian Quack, 2016, &ldquo;Playful
Locative Ensembles in the Urban Soundscapes &rdquo;,
<em>Navigationen-Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Medien-und
Kulturwissenschaften</em> 16(1): 85&ndash;100.</li>

<li>Tavinor, Grant, 2009, <em>The Art of Videogames</em>, Malden, MA:
Wiley-Blackwell.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2019, &ldquo;On Virtual
Transparency&rdquo;. <em>The Journal of Aesthetics and Art
Criticism</em>, 77(2): 145&ndash;156.</li>

<li>TeamLab, 2008, &ldquo;Universe of Water Particles on a Rock where
People Gather&rdquo; [website description], Tokyo: Japan.
 [<a href="https://borderless.teamlab.art/ew/iwa-waterparticles/" target="other">available online</a>].</li>
 
<li>Thomasson, Amie L., 2010, &ldquo;Ontological Innovation in
Art&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Aesthetics and Art Criticism</em>, 68(2):
119&ndash;30.</li>

<li>Thomson-Jones, Katherine, 2013, &ldquo;Sensing Motion in
Movies&rdquo;, in <em>Psychocinematics: Exploring Cognition at the
Movies</em>, A.P. Shimamura (ed.), Oxford: Oxford University Press,
pp. 115&ndash;32.</li>

<li>Thomson-Jones, Katherine, 2021, <em>Image in the Making: Digital
Innovation and the Visual Arts</em>, New York: Oxford University
Press.</li>
 
<li>Wilken, Rowan, 2019, <em>Cultural Economies of Locative
Media</em>. Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Zeimbekis, John, 2012, &ldquo;Digital Pictures, Sampling, and
Vagueness: The Ontology of Digital Pictures&rdquo;, <em>Journal of
Aesthetics and Art Criticism</em>, 70(1): 43&ndash;53.</li>
</ul>
</div> 

